<item>
            <title>[FLINK-1608] TaskManagers may pick wrong network interface when starting before JobManager</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-1608</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The TaskManager uses a NetUtils routine to pick a network interface that lets it talk to the Jobmanager. However, if the JobManager is not online yet, the TaskManager falls back to an arbitrary non-localhost device.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In cases where the TaskManagers start faster than the JobManager, they may pick the wrong interface (and associated address and hostname)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The later logic (that tries to connect to the JobManager actor) does several retries. I think we need similar logic when looking for a suitable network interface to use.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
